ent-RMCJumpsuitFreelancer-name = freelancer fatigues
ent-RMCJumpsuitFreelancer-desc = A set of loose-fitting fatigues, perfect for an informal mercenary. Smells like gunpowder, apple pie, and covered in grease and sake stains.

ent-RMCJumpsuitMarsoc-name = special operative uniform
ent-RMCJumpsuitMarsoc-desc = A black uniform for elite Marine personnel. Designed to be comfortable and help blend into dark environments.

ent-RMCJumpsuitMercenaryEngineer-name = mercenary engineer fatigues
ent-RMCJumpsuitMercenaryEngineer-desc = A blue suit with yellow accents, used by engineers. There is an unknown symbol emblazed on the suit.

ent-RMCJumpsuitMercenaryMiner-name = mercenary miner fatigues
ent-RMCJumpsuitMercenaryMiner-desc = A beige suit with a red armband. It looks a little thin, like it wasn't designed for protection. There is an unknown symbol emblazed on the suit.

ent-RMCJumpsuitMercenaryHeavy-name = mercenary fatigues
ent-RMCJumpsuitMercenaryHeavy-desc = A thick, beige suit with a red armband. There is an unknown symbol emblazed on the suit.

ent-RMCJumpsuitDutchBandolier-name = hunting clothes
ent-RMCJumpsuitDutchBandolier-desc = A set of tailored clothes, made from fine but sturdy reinforced fabrics. Protects from thorns, weather, and the cuts and scrapes that forever bedevil outdoorsmen.

ent-RMCJumpsuitDutch-name = Dutch's Dozen uniform
ent-RMCJumpsuitDutch-desc = A comfortable uniform worn by the Dutch's Dozen mercenaries. It's seen some definite wear and tear, but is still in good condition.

